at%20many%20were%20likely%C2%A0to%20have%20been%20Russian%20jamming%20and%20spoofing%20attacks.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEstonia%2C%20Latvia%2C%20Lithuania%2C%20Poland%2C%20T%C3%BCrkiye%2C%20and%20Cyprus%20are%20all%20at%20high%20risk%20of%20the%20attacks%2C%20per%20the%20report.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThousands%20of%20planes%20may%20have%20run%20into%20issues%20with%20jammed%20GPS%20signals%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20by%20British%20tabloid%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thesun.co.uk%2Fnews%2F27456029%2Frussia-hack-british-flights-air-safety-threat%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Sun%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20suggests%20that%20Russia%20may%20be%20to%20blame.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlanes%20reported%20about%2046%2C000%20instances%20of%20problems%20with%20their%20satellite%20navigation%20over%20the%20Baltics%20between%20August%202023%20and%20the%20end%20of%20March%202024%2C%20The%20Sun%20reported%2C%20using%20flight-log%20data%20from%20GPSJAM.org.%20Many%20of%20these%20were%20likely%20to%20have%20been%20jamming%20and%20spoofing%20attacks%2C%20The%20Sun%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJamming%20is%20an%20intentional%20radio%20frequency%20interference%20with%20global%20navigation%20satellite%20systems%20(GNSS)%20that%20prevents%20planes%20from%20accessing%20satellite%20signals%20and%20makes%20the%20GNSS%20system%20%26quot%3Bineffective%20or%20degraded%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20European%20Union%20Aviation%20Safety%20Agency%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpoofing%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20occurs%20when%20false%20satellite%20signals%20are%20sent%20to%20%26quot%3Bdeceive%26quot%3B%20GNSS%20receivers%20and%20cause%20them%20to%20compute%20incorrect%20position%2C%20navigation%2C%20and%20timing%20data%2C%20the%20EASA%20says.%20The%20Sun%20reported%20that%20in%20some%20cases%20planes%20swerved%20around%20objects%20that%20weren't%20actually%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20The%20Sun%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fbusiness%2F2024%2Fapr%2F22%2Fthousands-of-flights-to-and-from-europe-affected-by-suspected-russian-jamming%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Guardian%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20that%20Russia%20is%20suspected%20of%20being%20involved%20in%20GPS%20jamming%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20The%20Sun%2C%20Estonia%2C%20Latvia%2C%20Lithuania%2C%20Poland%2C%20T%C3%BCrkiye%2C%20and%20Cyprus%20are%20all%20at%20high%20risk%20of%20the%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBetween%20August%202023%20and%20the%20end%20of%20March%202024%2C%20more%20than%202%2C300%20Ryanair%20flights%20and%20more%20than%201%2C350%20flights%20by%20Hungarian%20budget%20carrier%20Wizz%20Air%20reported%20satnav%20problems%20in%20the%20Baltic%20region%2C%20per%20The%20Sun.%20The%20frequency%20of%20instances%20of%20navigation%20problems%20rocketed%20from%20fewer%20than%2050%20a%20week%20last%20year%20to%20more%20than%20350%20a%20week%20last%20month%2C%20The%20Sun%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20March%2C%20a%20Royal%20Air%20Force%20plane%20that%20UK%20Defense%20Secretary%20Grant%20Shapps%20was%20flying%20on%20from%20Poland%20to%20the%20UK%20%26quot%3Btemporarily%20experienced%20GPS%20jamming%26quot%3B%20when%20it%20flew%20close%20to%20Kaliningrad%2C%20a%20Russian%20exclave%20in%20the%20Baltics%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20British%20Prime%20Minister%20Rishi%20Sunak%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fpolitics%2F2024%2Fmar%2F14%2Frussia-suspected-of-jamming-gps-signal-on-aircraft-carrying-grant-shapps%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20been%20a%20%26quot%3Bsharp%20rise%26quot%3B%20in%20attacks%20on%20GNSSs%2C%20Luc%20Tytgat%2C%20the%20acting%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20EASA%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.easa.europa.eu%2Fen%2Fnewsroom-and-events%2Fpress-releases%2Feasa-partners-iata-counter-aviation-safety-threat-gnss-spoofing%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20January.%20The%20EASA%20noted%20that%20the%20uptick%20in%20jamming%20and%20spoofing%20incidents%20had%20%26quot%3Bincreasingly%20threatened%20the%20integrity%26quot%3B%20of%20positioning%2C%20navigation%2C%20and%20timing%20services%20across%20Eastern%20Europe%20and%20the%20Middle%20East.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20safety%20information%20bulletin%20in%20November%2C%20the%20EASA%20noted%20that%20the%20rise%20in%20jamming%20and%20spoofing%20had%20started%20in%20February%202022%2C%20the%20month%20that%20Russia%20invaded%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20issue%20particularly%20affects%20the%20geographical%20areas%20surrounding%20conflict%20zones%26quot%3B%20but%20is%20also%20encountered%20in%20parts%20of%20the%20Mediterranean%2C%20the%20Black%20Sea%2C%20the%20Baltic%20Sea%2C%20and%20the%20Arctic%20area%2C%20the%20EASA%20said.%20It%20noted%20that%20in%20the%20Baltic%20Sea%20area%20this%20affected%20flight%20information%20regions%20surrounding%20Kaliningrad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20CAA%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.independent.co.uk%2Ftravel%2Fnews-and-advice%2Fryanair-flights-russia-target-system-b2532516.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Independent%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20jamming%20and%20spoofing%20near%20conflict%20zones%20were%20often%20by-products%20of%20military%20activity%2C%20not%20deliberate%20actions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGPS%20jamming%20does%20not%20directly%20impact%20the%20navigation%20of%20an%20aircraft%20and%20while%20it's%20a%20known%20issue%2C%20this%20does%20not%20mean%20an%20aircraft%20has%20been%20jammed%20deliberately%2C%26quot%3B%20Glenn%20Bradley%2C%20head%20of%20flight%20operations%20at%20the%20UK%20Civil%20Aviation%20Authority%2C%20told%20The%20Sun.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Ryanair%20spokesperson%20told%20The%20Sun%20that%20if%20location%20systems%2C%20such%20as%20GPS%2C%20were%20not%20functioning%2C%20the%20crew%20would%20switch%20to%20alternate%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsid