t-settlement-housing-market-homebuying-agents-commissions-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%24418%20million%20settlement%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20aggrieved%20home%20sellers%20who%20sued%20the%20organization%20over%20the%20commissions%20they'd%20paid%20to%20real-estate%20agents.%20The%20deal%20could%20open%20the%20door%20for%20more%20consumers%20to%20bargain%20down%20those%20fees%20or%20nudge%20some%20people%20looking%20for%20a%20new%20home%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-rule-of-home-buying-fire-your-real-estate-agent-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eforgo%20an%20agent%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Given%20their%20revolutionary%20nature%2C%20the%20proposed%20rule%20changes%20%E2%80%94%20which%20still%20need%20approval%20from%20a%20federal%20judge%20%E2%80%94%20have%20also%20prompted%20a%20flood%20of%20questions%20about%20the%20future%20of%20homebuying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20very%20fluid%20situation%2C%26quot%3B%20Whitt%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuying%20a%20home%20has%20never%20come%20with%20a%20handy%20road%20map.%20But%20one%20thing%20is%20clear%3A%20It's%20about%20to%20get%20a%20lot%20murkier.%20With%20that%20in%20mind%2C%20I've%20been%20asking%20experts%20how%20buyers%20can%20prepare%20for%20whatever%20world%20comes%20next.%20Their%20answers%20illuminated%20the%20potential%20pitfalls%2C%20of%20which%20there%20are%20many.%20They%20also%20highlighted%20new%20ways%20to%20come%20out%20ahead%20%E2%80%94%20and%20maybe%20save%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20along%20the%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20you're%20ready%20to%20turn%20your%20late-night%20Zillow%20scrolling%20into%20a%20proper%20home%20search.%20Before%20you%20begin%20the%20journey%20in%20earnest%2C%20you%20should%20ask%20yourself%3A%20Do%20I%20want%20to%20hire%20an%20agent%3F%20There's%20a%20good%20chance%20the%20answer%20is%20yes%20%E2%80%94%20buying%20a%20home%20is%20a%20complicated%2C%20emotional%20transaction%20that%20usually%20benefits%20from%20an%20experienced%20set%20of%20eyes.%20Last%20year%2C%2089%25%20of%20buyers%20enlisted%20the%20help%20of%20a%20licensed%20agent%2C%20according%20to%20the%20NAR.%20Even%20Steve%20Brobeck%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20Consumer%20Federation%20of%20America%20and%20an%20outspoken%20critic%20of%20the%20real-estate%20industry%2C%20told%20me%20he%20wouldn't%20buy%20a%20home%20without%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20conventional%20wisdom%20%E2%80%94%20that%20it%20doesn't%20cost%20a%20buyer%20anything%20to%20hire%20an%20agent%20and%20that%20you%20need%20one%20to%20secure%20your%20dream%20home%20%E2%80%94%20is%20crumbling.%20Sites%20such%20as%20Zillow%20and%20Redfin%20have%20democratized%20the%20home%20search%2C%20while%20the%20recent%20lawsuits%20have%20exposed%20the%20billions%20of%20dollars%20that%20US%20consumers%20pay%20their%20agents%20every%20year.%20Some%20critics%20argue%20that%20buyers%20could%20be%20better%20served%20(and%20save%20a%20lot%20of%20cash)%20by%20instead%20hiring%20a%20lawyer%20for%20a%20few%20hours%20to%20look%20over%20contracts%20and%20make%20sure%20everything%20is%20in%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20buyers%20probably%20don't%20have%20that%20kind%20of%20confidence%2C%20especially%20first-timers.%20If%20you%20fall%20into%20that%20camp%2C%20the%20next%20step%20is%20to%20figure%20out%20exactly%20which%20kinds%20of%20services%20you'll%20need.%20Maybe%20you%20feel%20certain%20that%20you%20can%20find%20and%20tour%20homes%20on%20your%20own%20but%20want%20someone%20to%20manage%20the%20transaction%20and%20make%20sure%20you%20don't%20skip%20over%20any%20crucial%20to-dos.%20Or%20maybe%20you%20want%20a%20more%20involved%20agent%20who%20can%20send%20you%20listings%2C%20guide%20you%20through%20homes%2C%20help%20you%20line%20up%20inspections%20and%20a%20mortgage%2C%20and%20haggle%20with%20the%20seller%20over%20every%20last%20detail%20%E2%80%94%20someone%20whose%20%26quot%3Bwhole%20job%20is%20to%20be%20nosy%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20Sabrina%20Brown%2C%20a%20broker%20in%20North%20Carolina%2C%20told%20me.%20Those%20are%20two%20very%20different%20job%20descriptions%2C%20but%20they've%20traditionally%20commanded%20pretty%20much%20the%20same%20fee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224861%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Rows%20of%20suburban%20homes%20in%20Ocala%2C%20Florida%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652069656e038039826c5948%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223131%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EReal-estate%20agents'%20commissions%20have%20fluctuated%20between%205%25%20and%206%25%20of%20the%20sale%20price%20for%20decades%2C%20despite%20advances%20in%20technology%20and%20an%20influx%20of%20agents.%3Cp%3EMichael%20Warren%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDiscerning%20buyers%20could%20upend%20that%20status%20quo.%20Once%20you%20figure%20out%20what%20you%20want%20out%20of%20an%20agent%2C%20you'll%20have%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20much%20you're%20willing%20to%20pay%20for%20them.%20Prepare%20to%20have%20a%20frank%20conversation%20with%20prospective%20agents.%20For%20decades%2C%20homebuyers%20have%20coasted%20on%20the%20blissful%20assumption%20that%20using%20an%20agent%20is%20free.%20This%20illusion%20was%20maintained%20by%20the%20roundabout%20way%20in%20which%20money%20trades%20hands%3A%20The%20typical%20buyer%20never%20pays%20their%20agent%20directly%3B%20instead%2C%20the%20seller%20pays%20their%20own%20agent%2C%20who%20then%20uses%20part%20of%20that%20commission%20check%20to%20pay%20out%20the%20buyer's%20agent.%20Ultimately%2C%20the%20commission%20comes%20out%20of%20the%20money%20the%20buyer%20sent%20to%20the%20seller%2C%20but%20the%20transaction%20is%20hidden.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESellers%20agreed%20to%20this%20method%20because%20they%20didn't%20want%20to%20risk%20having%20their%20homes%20passed%20over%20by%20buyers'%20agents%20who%20might%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-agent-commissions-steering-hiding-homes-housing-market-lawsuits-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bsteer%26quot%3B%20their%20clients%3C%2Fa%3E%20away%20from%20properties%20that%20didn't%20offer%20compensation%20to%20the%20other%20side%20or%20offered%20sums%20lower%20than%20standard%20commission%20rates%2C%20usually%205%25%20to%206%25%20of%20the%20total%20home%20price.%20And%20because%20buyers%20weren't%20paying%20their%20agents%20directly%2C%20they%20usually%20didn't%20see%20much%20reason%20to%20bargain%20down%20the%20fee.%20In%20fact%2C%20they%20might%20not%20even%20know%20their%20agent's%20rate%20until%20they're%20at%20the%20closing%20table%2C%20if%20they%20ever%20found%20out%20at%20all.%20This%20model%20has%20proved%20lucrative%20for%20agents.%20Buyers%20and%20sellers%20typically%20pay%20more%20than%20%24100%20billion%20a%20year%20to%20the%20real-estate%20industry%2C%20a%20massive%20wealth%20transfer%20that%20Brobeck%20estimated%20could%20be%20cut%20down%20by%20about%20%2430%20billion%20annually%20if%20commissions%20were%20in%20line%20with%20America's%20peers%20like%20the%20United%20Kingdom%20or%20Australia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20lawsuits%2C%20which%20accused%20the%20NAR%20and%20some%20of%20the%20country's%20largest%20brokerages%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-agents-lawsuits-buy-sell-homes-forever-housing-market-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econspiring%20to%20keep%20agents'%20commissions%20unfairly%20high%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20could%20signal%20the%20start%20of%20a%20new%20era.%20As%20part%20of%20its%20deal%20to%20settle%20the%20cases%2C%20the%20NAR%20agreed%20to%20prohibit%20sellers'%20agents%20from%20making%20offers%20of%20commission%20to%20buyers'%20agents%20on%20the%20multiple-listings%20services%2C%20the%20local%20databases%20where%20agents%20can%20browse%20homes%20and%20see%20how%20much%20they%20stand%20to%20collect%20on%20a%20deal.%20The%20organization%20also%20agreed%20to%20require%20its%20members%20to%20negotiate%20commissions%20with%20their%20buyer%20clients%20in%20writing%20before%20so%20much%20as%20showing%20them%20a%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20with%20these%20changes%2C%20the%20settlement%2C%20which%20is%20set%20to%20go%20into%20effect%20in%20July%20if%20approved%2C%20doesn't%20contain%20a%20single%20rule%20that%20would%20kill%20off%20the%206%25%20commission%20on%20its%20own.%20A%20deal%20like%20this%20simply%20can't%20solve%20all%20the%20industry's%20problems%20in%20one%20fell%20swoop%2C%20Prentiss%20Cox%2C%20a%20law%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Minnesota%2C%20said%20recently%20in%20a%20public%20forum%20he%20convened%20to%20discuss%20the%20coming%20changes.%20In%20many%20instances%2C%20agents%20might%20proceed%20with%20business%20as%20usual%2C%20and%20consumers%20could%20still%20end%20up%20paying%20today's%20standard%20commission%20rates.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20it'll%20be%20up%20to%20savvy%20buyers%20to%20find%20ways%20to%20make%20this%20deal%20work%20in%20their%20favor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20NAR%20has%20always%20argued%20that%20commissions%20are%20negotiable.%20That%20may%20be%20true%20in%20theory%2C%20but%20buyers%20rarely%20take%20advantage%20of%20that%20right.%20It's%20worth%20a%20shot%2C%20though%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20the%20seller%20is%20the%20one%20who%20pays%20out%20both%20agents%20after%20the%20deal%20closes%2C%20the%20money%20you%20bring%20to%20the%20table%20is%20ultimately%20footing%20the%20bill.%20If%20you%20negotiate%20a%20lower%20fee%2C%20you%20could%20get%20some%20money%20back%20from%20your%20agent%20in%20the%20form%20of%20a%20rebate%20after%20the%20sale%20closes.%20Alternatively%2C%20you%20might%20be%20able%20to%20bargain%20down%20the%20home%20price%20by%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20if%20the%20seller%20knows%20they'll%20have%20to%20set%20aside%20less%20money%20for%20agent%20commissions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaybe%20you're%20the%20kind%20of%20buyer%20who%20wants%20someone%20to%20hold%20your%20hand%20through%20every%20step%20of%20the%20process%2C%20in%20which%20case%20the%20traditional%202.5%25%20to%203%25%20for%20your%20agent%20might%20be%20a%20good%20deal.%20But%20if%20you've%20found%20a%20home%20and%20just%20need%20help%20making%20sure%20the%20deal%20doesn't%20go%20off%20the%20rails%2C%20you%20stand%20a%20greater%20chance%20of%20scoring%20a%20lower%20fee%20from%20your%20agent.%20There%20are%20also%20various%20discount%20brokerages%20that%20charge%20lower%20commission%20rates%2C%20even%20flat%20fees%2C%20in%20exchange%20for%20a%20more%20bare-bones%20approach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBear%20in%20mind%20that%20an%20agent%20isn't%20obligated%20to%20lower%20their%20commission%20in%20the%20same%20way%20that%20a%20lawyer%20doesn't%20have%20to%20cut%20down%20their%20hourly%20fee%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20you%20ask%20nicely.%20But%20they%20may%20be%20inclined%20to%20do%20so%20if%20they%20really%20want%20your%20business.%20And%20if%20not%2C%20well%2C%20there%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbad-real-estate-agents-realtors-homebuyers-sellers-housing-market-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emany%20other%20agents%20out%20there%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20would%20probably%20love%20the%20chance%20to%20help%20you%20with%20your%20home%20purchase.%20Interview%20agents%20as%20if%20you%20were%20a%20boss%20hiring%20them%20for%20a%20job%2C%20which%20is%20exactly%20what%20you're%20doing.%20Don't%20shy%20away%20from%20the%20tough%20questions.%20Jack%20Ryan%2C%20a%20cofounder%20and%20the%20CEO%20of%20the%20discount%20brokerage%20Rex%20Real%20Estate%2C%20suggested%20one%20query%3A%20Ask%20your%20agent%20why%20they're%20worth%203%25%20of%20the%20home's%20sale%20price%20%E2%80%94%20after%20all%2C%20that's%20equal%20to%20%2415%2C000%20on%20a%20%24500%2C000%20home.%20Some%20will%20have%20a%20great%20answer%2C%20others%2C%20not%20so%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Realtors%20keep%20saying%2C%20'Oh%2C%20we%20deserve%20our%203%25%20fee%2C'%26quot%3B%20Ryan%2C%20whose%20company%20shuttered%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzillow-realtors-accused-anticompetitive-practices-rex-lawsuit-texas-real-estate-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elegal%20battle%20with%20the%20NAR%20and%20Zillow%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BWell%2C%20maybe%20you%20do.%20Convince%20the%20buyer%20that%20you%20do.%20And%20if%20you%20can%20add%203%25%20of%20value%2C%20great.%20But%20why%20are%20you%20claiming%20you%20know%20what%20you're%20worth%20relative%20to%20what%20the%20market%20says%20you're%20worth%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20brave%20new%20world%20of%20homebuying%20won't%20guarantee%20easy%20wins%20for%20consumers.%20The%20path%20to%20homeownership%20is%20still%20lined%20with%20plenty%20of%20hazards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20while%20listing%20agents%20%E2%80%94%20those%20who%20represent%20the%20seller%20%E2%80%94%20are%20set%20to%20be%20prohibited%20from%20offering%20commissions%20to%20buyers'%20agents%20via%20the%20MLS%20databases%2C%20they%20can%20still%20disclose%20commissions%20pretty%20much%20anywhere%20else%3A%20on%20their%20websites%2C%20on%20a%20phone%20call%2C%20or%20even%20in%20person%20at%20an%20open%20house.%20A%20seller%20just%20wants%20to%20get%20the%20best%20price%20for%20their%20home%20as%20quickly%20as%20possible%2C%20Rob%20Hahn%2C%20a%20longtime%20industry%20consultant%2C%20said%20during%20the%20University%20of%20Minnesota%20forum.%20To%20make%20sure%20their%20house%20is%20seen%2C%20the%20standard%20commission%20might%20be%20a%20necessary%20pill%20to%20swallow.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-housing-market-home-prices-mortgage-rates-home-affordability-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esellers%20in%20hot%20markets%3C%2Fa%3E%20might%20feel%20like%20they%20could%20save%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20by%20offering%20less%20to%20a%20buyer's%20agent%20%E2%80%94%20maybe%201%25%20instead%20of%20the%20typical%202%25%20or%203%25%20%E2%80%94%20or%20even%20nothing%20at%20all.%20If%20people%20are%20falling%20over%20themselves%20to%20get%20into%20your%20home%2C%20why%20dangle%20money%20in%20front%20of%20buyers'%20agents%20just%20to%20get%20them%20through%20the%20door%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20why%20buyers%20can%20no%20longer%20afford%20to%20remain%20in%20the%20dark%20about%20how%20their%20agents%20get%20paid%20and%20how%20much.%20If%20sellers%20aren't%20paying%20out%20commissions%20to%20buyers'%20agents%2C%20buyers%20themselves%20could%20end%20up%20on%20the%20hook.%20To%20avoid%20this%20kind%20of%20surprise%20and%20lay%20out%20the%20terms%20of%20their%20representation%2C%20buyers'%20agents%20will%20have%20to%20get%20their%20clients%20to%20sign%20what's%20known%20as%20a%20buyer-agency%20contract.%20Some%20states%20already%20require%20these%20contracts%2C%20but%20a%20lot%20of%20agents%20in%20other%20places%20never%20use%20them%3A%20Only%2041%25%20of%20buyers%20last%20year%20said%20they%20signed%20a%20buyer-agency%20agreement%2C%20according%20to%20the%20NAR.%20This%20might%20be%20a%20more%20prudent%20move%20than%20buyers%20even%20realize%20%E2%80%94%20most%20of%20the%20agreements%20floating%20around%20today%20were%20created%20by%20state%20Realtor%20associations%20and%20are%20therefore%20designed%20to%20protect%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20agent%2C%20Wendy%20Gilch%2C%20a%20consumer%20advocate%2C%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20if%20someone%20presents%20you%20with%20some%20printed%20form%2C%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20it's%20set%20in%20stone%2C%26quot%3B%20Gilch%2C%20who%20focuses%20on%20transparency%20in%20real%20estate%20through%20her%20company%2C%20Selling%20Later%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20decline%20it%20and%20be%20like%2C%20'No%2C%20I'm%20not%20going%20to%20sign%20that.%20Change%20this%3B%20change%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuyer-agency%20contracts%20don't%20have%20to%20be%20tilted%20in%20favor%20of%20Realtors.%20In%20fact%2C%20if%20used%20fairly%2C%20they%20can%20provide%20transparency%20and%20clarity%20for%20both%20buyers%20and%20their%20agents.%20Under%20the%20terms%20of%20the%20recent%20NAR%20settlement%2C%20these%20contracts%20would%20have%20to%20include%20a%20few%20things.%20First%2C%20a%20buyer%20and%20their%20agent%20would%20need%20to%20agree%20to%20the%20maximum%20amount%20of%20compensation%20that%20the%20buyer's%20agent%20can%20receive%20%E2%80%94%20this%20could%20be%20something%20like%20a%20certain%20percentage%20of%20the%20sale%20price%2C%20an%20hourly%20rate%2C%20or%20a%20flat%20fee%20if%20the%20agent%20is%20willing%20to%20accept%20that.%20If%20the%20buyer%20and%20their%20agent%20agree%20to%2C%20say%2C%202%25%20of%20the%20sale%20price%2C%20the%20agent%20can't%20accept%20any%20more%20than%20that.%20The%20buyer's%20agent%20would%20also%20have%20to%20update%20the%20client%2C%20in%20writing%2C%20on%20how%20much%20commission%20they%20stand%20to%20receive%20from%20the%20house%20their%20client%20is%20pursuing.%20On%20the%20whole%2C%20these%20look%20like%20positive%20steps%20for%20consumers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20always%2C%20though%2C%20the%20devil%20is%20in%20the%20details.%20For%20example%2C%20what%20happens%20if%20the%20seller%20isn't%20willing%20to%20pay%20the%20buyer's%20agent's%20commission%3F%20In%20many%20cases%2C%20the%20template%20forms%20provided%20by%20the%20state%20Realtor%20associations%20say%20the%20buyer%20is%20responsible%20for%20covering%20the%20difference%20between%20what%20the%20buyer's%20agent%20expects%20to%20receive%20and%20what%20the%20seller%20is%20offering%20to%20pay.%20This%20could%20leave%20buyers%20on%20the%20hook%20to%20pay%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20out%20of%20their%20own%20pockets.%20A%20report%20from%20the%20Consumer%20Federation%20of%20America%20pointed%20out%20other%20risks%3A%20Buyers%20might%20not%20have%20a%20good%20way%20to%20get%20out%20of%20the%20contract%20if%20they're%20unsatisfied%20with%20their%20agent%2C%20or%20they%20might%20unwittingly%20agree%20to%20pay%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-junk-fees-home-buying-house-prices-more-expensive-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bjunk%20fees%2C%26quot%3B%20such%20as%20an%20administrative%20fee%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20can%20cost%20anywhere%20between%20several%20hundred%20dollars%20and%20nearly%20%241%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20more%20scenario%20to%20consider%3A%20What%20happens%20if%20a%20seller%20is%20offering%203%25%20of%20the%20price%20to%20a%20buyer's%20agent%2C%20but%20you%20and%20your%20agent%20agreed%20to%20a%20max%20of%202%25%3F%20In%20most%20states%2C%20the%20buyer's%20agent%20can%20technically%20just%20rebate%20that%20extra%20money%20to%20their%20client.%20These%20kinds%20of%20rebates%20may%20be%20rare%20these%20days%2C%20but%20they%20could%20become%20more%20common%20after%20this%20settlement.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20in%20a%20mind-boggling%20twist%2C%20nine%20states%20prohibit%20rebates%20entirely.%20That%20needs%20to%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20important%20thing%20for%20buyers%20entering%20this%20new%20market%2C%20experts%20told%20me%2C%20is%20to%20read%20the%20buyer-agency%20contract%20carefully%20or%20consider%20hiring%20a%20lawyer%20if%20you%20have%20concerns.%20Realtors%20may%20rely%20on%20templates%20handed%20down%20from%20their%20state%20associations%2C%20but%20the%20terms%20aren't%20ironclad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20all%20this%20sounds%20intimidating%2C%20rest%20assured%3A%20Even%20the%20people%20who%20live%20and%20breathe%20this%20stuff%20are%20struggling%20to%20make%20sense%20of%20it.%20David%20Dworkin%2C%20the%20president%20and%20CEO%20of%20the%20National%20Housing%20Conference%2C%20called%20the%20settlement%20%26quot%3Bthe%20most%20opaque%20and%20complicated%20agreement%20I%20have%20ever%20encountered.%26quot%3B%20Dworkin%20told%20me%20he%20feared%20the%20deal%20would%20favor%20higher-income%20buyers%20and%20sellers%20who%20might%20be%20able%20to%20claim%20larger%20discounts%20from%20agents%20who%20stand%20to%20make%20a%20bunch%20of%20money%20off%20them%20regardless.%20But%20the%20bigger%20issue%20is%20that%20nobody%20has%20any%20idea%20how%20buyers%20and%20sellers%20would%20react%20to%20these%20proposed%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDepending%20on%20how%20you%20look%20at%20it%2C%20that's%20either%20aggravating%20or%20exciting.%20Regardless%2C%20the%20lawsuits%20have%20undoubtedly%20exposed%20market%20corruption%2C%20said%20Cox%2C%20the%20University%20of%20Minnesota%20law%20professor.%20All%20this%20focus%20on%20commissions%20could%20hasten%20a%20new%20era%20of%20experimentation%20in%20real%20estate%2C%20in%20which%20buyers'%20agents%20offer%20varying%20levels%20of%20service%20or%20commission%20rates%20in%20a%20bid%20to%20win%20clients.%20The%20revolution%20is%20only%20beginning%3B%20recently%2C%20the%20Justice%20Department%20got%20clearance%20to%20reopen%20its%20investigation%20into%20the%20NAR's%20practices%2C%20meaning%20more%20changes%20could%20be%20on%20the%20horizon.%20In%20this%20sense%2C%20the%20mere%20fact%20that%20more%20people%20are%20talking%20about%20commissions%20is%20a%20win.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20advice%20I%20got%20from%20experts%20can%20be%20boiled%20down%20to%20a%20simple%20mantra%3A%20Get%20in%20on%20that%20conversation.%20Talk%20to%20your%20agent%20early%20on%20in%20the%20process%20about%20the%20services%20you%20want%2C%20and%20make%20sure%20you're%20on%20the%20same%20page%20about%20their%20commissions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20the%20solution.%20It's%20the%20first%20step%20in%20attacking%20this%20problem%2C%26quot%3B%20Cox%20said%20of%20the%20recent%20settlement.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20it's%20been%20spectacularly%20successful%20in%20being%20the%20first%20step.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fjames-rodriguez%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EJames%20Rodri