O.%20Here's%20what%20it's%20like%20running%20a%20company%20in%20the%20happiest%20country%20on%20earth.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223940%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Helsinki%20Finland%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5fea08e2edf8920018093dc6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222953%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EMiemo%20Penttinen%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fin%2Fsamu-h%25C3%25A4llfors-67240a6%3ForiginalSubdomain%3Dfi%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESamu%20H%C3%A4llfors%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20the%20CEO%20of%20Framery%2C%20an%20office%20soundproofing%20business%20in%20Helsinki.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EH%C3%A4llfors%20mirrors%20how%20he%20runs%20his%20company%20in%20line%20with%20Finnish%20values%20like%20shared%20responsibility.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20said%20people%20in%20Finland%20are%20hard%20working%20and%20candid%2C%20with%20strong%20boundaries%20between%20work%20and%20home.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20transcribed%20conversation%20with%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fin%2Fsamu-h%25C3%25A4llfors-67240a6%3ForiginalSubdomain%3Dfi%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESamu%20H%C3%A4llfors%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20the%20CEO%20of%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.frameryacoustics.com%2Fen%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EFramery%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20in%20Helsinki.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202010%2C%20I%20worked%20at%20Logia%20Software%20Oy%20in%20an%20open%20office%20space.%20My%20friend%20and%20I%20were%20tired%20of%20constantly%20listening%20to%20our%20boss%20speak%20on%20his%20phone.%20It%20was%20impossible%20to%20focus%20on%20our%20work.%20When%20we%20brought%20it%20up%2C%20our%20boss%20responded%3A%20%26quot%3BWell%2C%20buy%20me%20a%20phone%20booth.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20problem%20was%20that%20there%20wasn't%20one%20on%20the%20market.%20We%20gave%20up%20working%20for%20the%20software%20company%20that%20day%2C%20and%20Framery%20was%20born.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFramery%20is%20a%2014-year-old%20company%20headquartered%20in%20my%20homeland%20of%20Finland%20that%20offers%20soundproof%20solutions%20for%20offices.%20Our%20office%20is%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-finland-happiest-place-never-visited-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHelsinki%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20CEO%20of%20a%20company%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffinland-the-happiest-country-in-the-world-seventh-year-running-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20world's%20happiest%20country%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20mirrored%20my%20company's%20values%20and%20policies%20with%20many%20of%20the%20Finnish%20cultural%20aspects%20I%20admire.%20Here%20are%20some%20ways%20I'm%20running%20Framery%20in%20line%20with%20those%20values.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMutual%20responsibility%20makes%20people%20feel%20safe%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20multiple%20parallels%20between%20Finnish%20society%20and%20how%20we've%20built%20culture%20at%20Framery%2C%20starting%20with%20psychological%20safety.%20A%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rd.com%2Flist%2Fmost-honest-cities-lost-wallet-test%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReaders'%20Digest%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20a%20report%20about%20a%20social%20experiment%20where%2012%20wallets%20were%20intentionally%20%26quot%3Bdropped%26quot%3B%20in%20various%20cities%20around%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Finland%2C%2011%20of%20those%2012%20wallets%20were%20returned%20to%20their%20owners.%20In%20Finnish%20society%2C%20people%20feel%20a%20general%20level%20of%20safety%20because%20the%20culture%20is%20focused%20on%20the%20collective%20responsibility%20to%20care%20for%20and%20be%20honest%20with%20each%20other%2C%20regardless%20of%20the%20relationship%20or%20how%20well%20we%20know%20someone.%20We%20are%20a%20close-knit%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20try%20to%20encourage%20this%20attitude%20at%20work.%20I%20never%20allow%20my%20employees%20to%20feel%20that%20mistakes%20or%20failures%20are%20their%20fault.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMistakes%20still%20happen.%20When%20they%20do%2C%20it's%20usually%20followed%20up%20with%20a%20discussion%20on%20how%20to%20remediate%20for%20the%20future.%20As%20long%20as%20the%20root%20cause%20of%20the%20mistake%20is%20not%20laziness%20or%20negligence%2C%20then%20the%20responsibility%20is%20shared%2C%20and%20there%20is%20no%20place%20for%20blame.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20want%20my%20employees%20to%20feel%20safe%20exploring%20new%20ideas%2C%20taking%20risks%2C%20and%20making%20mistakes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWork-life%20balance%20is%20a%20priority%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Finnish%20workday%20is%20usually%20eight%20hours%2C%20with%20a%20half-hour%20lunch%20break%2C%20so%20people%20have%20time%20for%20hobbies%20and%20leisure%20activities%20after%20work.%20In%20Finland%2C%20we%20believe%20there%20is%20a%20time%20to%20rest%20and%20work%3B%20regardless%20of%20what%20we%20are%20doing%2C%20we%20put%20our%20complete%20attention%20and%20concentration%20into%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20make%20it%20a%20point%20to%20visibly%20leave%20the%20office%20toward%20the%20end%20of%20the%20working%20day%20and%20to%20enforce%20strict%20rules%20around%20maximum%20working%20hours%20so%20that%20employees%20can%20enjoy%20work-life%20balance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%20projects%20may%20require%20extra%20hours%2C%20but%20employees%20are%20encouraged%20to%20balance%20their%20workweek%20by%20taking%20time%20off%20or%20long%20weekends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EExtreme%20candor%20for%20the%20benefit%20of%20the%20group%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Finns%20are%20very%20honest%20and%20direct%20people.%20Though%20this%20may%20come%20across%20as%20naive%20in%20other%20cultures%2C%20we%20value%20communicating%20candidly%2C%20independent%20thinking%2C%20and%20bearing%20responsibility%20accordingly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELarge%20corporations%20usually%20have%20layers%20of%20bureaucracy%20that%20determine%20who%20gets%20access%20to%20what%20information.%20That%20leads%20to%20a%20loss%20of%20shared%20purpose%2C%20the%20idea%20that%20people%20within%20the%20organization%20are%20all%20aligned%20to%20the%20same%20mission.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Framery%2C%20everyone%20gets%20to%20participate%20in%20our%20strategy%20deep%20dives.%20We%20share%20highly%20classified%20information%20with%20every%20employee%20so%20they%20have%20equal%20footing%20and%20more%20oversight%20on%20their%20day-to-day%20tasks.%20I%20always%20host%20the%20sessions%2C%20and%20there%20can%20be%20no%20more%20than%2012%20participants%20at%20once%2C%20so%20there's%20an%20opportunity%20to%20ask%20questions%20and%20debate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20the%20obvious%20risk%20of%20leaked%20information%2C%20but%20I%20trust%20my%20employees.%20I%20think%20there's%20a%20bigger%20risk%20in%20not%20telling%20people%20important%20information%20that%20will%20be%20helpful%20in%20their%20daily%20tasks.%20Plus%2C%20disclosing%20private%20employer%20information%20is%20illegal%2C%20and%20Finns%20understand%20their%20responsibilities%20toward%20their%20employer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECelebrate%20independent%20hard%20work%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20have%20recently%20become%20more%20stringent%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freturn-to-office-mandates-employees-managers-fight-messy-remote-work-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereturn-to-office%20policies%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20employee%20tracking%20tools.%20I%20view%20this%20as%20micromanagement%2C%20which%20destroys%20the%20individual's%20sense%20of%20autonomy%20and%20purpose.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinnish%20culture%20is%20deeply%20rooted%20in%20forward-thinking%20and%20preparation%2C%20stemming%20from%20their%20historical%20need%20to%20brace%20for%20harsh%2C%20protracted%20winters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20ingrained%20mindset%20fostered%20a%20strong%20work%20ethic%20among%20the%20Finns%2C%20born%20from%20the%20understanding%20that%20diligent%20effort%20paves%20the%20way%20for%20long-term%20career%20success%20and%20longevity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20our%20employees%20know%20better%20than%20their%20CEO%20on%20how%20to%20structure%20their%20personal%20workday.%20Teams%20can%20decide%20when%20they%20want%20to%20come%20into%20the%20office%20and%20how%20they%20plan%20to%20execute%20their%20work.%20They%20are%20mandated%20by%20themselves%2C%20not%20by%20management.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffinland-happiest-country-ceo-work-culture-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713863298000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5fea0907a64488001819378d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffinland-happiest-country-ceo-work-culture-2024-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Finland%20is%20the%20happiest%20place%20on%20earth.%20The%20CEO%20of%20a%20Helsinki%20business%20shares%20how%20he%20manages%20his%20company%20in%20line%20with%20Finnish%20culture.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Pooja%20Shah)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A16%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffinland-happiest-country-ceo-work-culture-2024-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Hesson%20reveals%20reason%20behind%20Chahal's%20departure%20from%20RCB%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713863201000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-109528087%2Cimgsize-54786.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofi